to get up for work at 6:00 a.m.

486
00:21:29.289 --> 00:21:31.332
- The customers suck.
- Mm-hmm.

487
00:21:31.333 --> 00:21:35.586
My hair smells like shrimp. Derek
happens to love the smell of shrimp.

488
00:21:35.587 --> 00:21:36.754
It's all bad.

489
00:21:36.755 --> 00:21:38.339
But I love that truck.

490
00:21:38.340 --> 00:21:39.507
Then what's the problem?

491
00:21:39.508 --> 00:21:43.554
Well. the problem is-is that I-I
think I wanna be a better person.

492
00:21:44.096 --> 00:21:45.179
Sometimes.

493
00:21:45.180 --> 00:21:46.597
Sometimes I don't give a shit.

494
00:21:46.598 --> 00:21:47.558
Oh. we know.

495
00:21:47.559 --> 00:21:51.894
It's just that now I know that Sean and
his dad always wanted to do this together.

496
00:21:51.895 --> 00:21:54.230
and I feel like I took
that away from them.

497
00:21:54.231 --> 00:21:56.524
Do you know what the theory
of psychological egoism is?

498
00:21:56.525 --> 00:21:57.984
[babbles]

499
00:21:57.985 --> 00:21:59.610
- I'm gonna take that as a no.
- No.

500
00:21:59.611 --> 00:22:03.823
But it's basically this idea that all
behavior is motivated by self-interest.

501
00:22:03.824 --> 00:22:07.618
and that we are all actually
inherently selfish people.

502
00:22:07.619 --> 00:22:11.247
and we do pretty much whatever
it is that makes us happy.

503
00:22:11.248 --> 00:22:14.083
So. it's up to you to figure
out where your joy lives.

504
00:22:14.084 --> 00:22:17.086
Is it in doing stuff
for other people?

505
00:22:17.087 --> 00:22:18.567
Or is it in doing
stuff for yourself?

506
00:22:20.674 --> 00:22:22.926
- Well. that was useless.
- Glad I could help.

507
00:22:23.844 --> 00:22:25.678
[Derek slurps]

508
00:22:25.679 --> 00:22:27.472
Oh. Hey. Paul.

509
00:22:28.599 --> 00:22:31.058
Derek. Liz's husband.

510
00:22:31.059 --> 00:22:32.603
How much did you eat?

511
00:22:33.353 --> 00:22:34.437
Not proud.

512
00:22:34.438 --> 00:22:35.898
But I'm also a little proud.

513
00:22:37.316 --> 00:22:38.691
Hey. Paul.

514
00:22:38.692 --> 00:22:42.070
Oh. good. I was just about to
give my workshop on boundaries.

515
00:22:42.571 --> 00:22:43.571
You'll be fine.

516
00:22:43.572 --> 00:22:46.574
Derek. I need to borrow your
car. I gotta go talk to somebody.

517
00:22:46.575 --> 00:22:47.951
Cool. I'll Uber home.

518
00:22:48.994 --> 00:22:50.746
- I'd like you to get your steps.
- Ah.

519
00:22:52.956 --> 00:22:54.333
When I get steps. I get a treat.

520
00:22:55.459 --> 00:22:56.793
Has to be fruit though.

521
00:22:57.461 --> 00:22:58.378
Hmm.

522
00:22:58.379 --> 00:23:01.215
[stammers. chuckles] You can
judge all you want. I'm happy.

523
00:23:02.090 --> 00:23:05.635
I've been watching couples around
us drop like flies for years.

524
00:23:05.636 --> 00:23:10.723
Well. you've managed to build a nice life
with someone who seems like a nightmare.

525
00:23:10.724 --> 00:23:12.017
No offense.

526
00:23:12.518 --> 00:23:15.019
She reminds me of me. [sighs]

527
00:23:15.020 --> 00:23:20.901
I'm prickly and stubborn. and that's
before you add the Parkinson's.

528
00:23:21.860 --> 00:23:24.820
Now. there's this woman. but
she's been through a lot.

529
00:23:24.821 --> 00:23:28.283
and I'm beginning to wonder
what we're even doing.

530
00:23:31.370 --> 00:23:34.581
Are you in love with this woman?

531
00:23:35.541 --> 00:23:37.417
- We have to go there?
- Yeah.

532
00:23:38.085 --> 00:23:39.086
Fine.

533
00:23:40.003 --> 00:23:41.712
I'm deeply in love.

534
00:23:41.713 --> 00:23:45.509
[chuckles] Ah.
the greatest gift.

535
00:23:46.093 --> 00:23:48.136
You have to do whatever
you can to protect it.

536
00:23:48.887 --> 00:23:51.681
Look. for me. I just let the stuff that
doesn't bother me bounce right off.

537
00:23:51.682 --> 00:23:54.559
And if there's anything
tricky that can be removed.

538
00:23:54.560 --> 00:23:56.060
we just get it the
heck out of there.

539
00:23:56.061 --> 00:23:59.106
So I'll just remove
the Parkinson's?

540
00:24:00.649 --> 00:24:02.358
Great advice. Thanks.

541
00:24:02.359 --> 00:24:03.694
[chuckles]

542
00:24:06.154 --> 00:24:08.407
You do remind me of Liz. Yeah.

543
00:24:13.120 --> 00:24:14.872
[customers chattering]

544
00:24:17.082 --> 00:24:18.292
Hey.

545
00:24:20.169 --> 00:24:21.170
Are you into MMA?

546
00:24:21.962 --> 00:24:23.004
What?

547
00:24:23.005 --> 00:24:24.298
Cool sweatshirt.

548
00:24:26.008 --> 00:24:28.718
- It's my mom's.
- Ah. Well. cool mum then.

549
00:24:28.719 --> 00:24:30.012
You want a coffee?

550
00:24:31.430 --> 00:24:33.807
Okay. One very mediocre
drip coming up.

551
00:24:34.641 --> 00:24:36.101
Do you really not know who I am?

552
00:24:38.896 --> 00:24:41.690
I'm sorry. No. [stammers] I
haven't been working here long.

553
00:24:42.274 --> 00:24:43.358
Just thought you might...

554
00:24:45.027 --> 00:24:46.278
because you killed my mom.

555
00:24:55.662 --> 00:24:57.496
Can you. um... Can
you cover for me?

556
00:24:57.497 --> 00:24:59.373
Why? So you can run away?

557
00:24:59.374 --> 00:25:00.709
No. No. I. um...

558
00:25:01.293 --> 00:25:03.252
I... I wanna talk.

559
00:25:03.253 --> 00:25:04.463
I... [stammers]

560
00:25:07.841 --> 00:25:08.884
How are you?

561
00:25:10.594 --> 00:25:11.719
That was dumb. I'm sorry.

562
00:25:11.720 --> 00:25:16.016
I. uh... I always hoped I'd get
the chance to speak to you someday.

563
00:25:17.893 --> 00:25:19.061
I want to say I'm sorry.

564
00:25:20.896 --> 00:25:26.526
I know that's not enough...
[stammers] ...or not right.

565
00:25:26.527 --> 00:25:28.070
I don't know. Um...

566
00:25:32.282 --> 00:25:33.783
I can't imagine
what you've been...

567
00:25:33.784 --> 00:25:35.118
Shut up!

568
00:25:36.745 --> 00:25:38.704
Shut the fuck up!

569
00:25:38.705 --> 00:25:40.082
[softly] Okay.

570
00:25:43.168 --> 00:25:44.377
Fuck you!

571
00:25:44.378 --> 00:25:45.963
[customers gasping]

572
00:25:59.643 --> 00:26:01.602
We should go to Marrakech.

573
00:26:01.603 --> 00:26:02.687
Okay.

574
00:26:02.688 --> 00:26:04.188
[knocks on door]

575
00:26:04.189 --> 00:26:05.565
Hey. Liz. You wanted to talk?

576
00:26:05.566 --> 00:26:06.983
Yep. Yep.

577
00:26:06.984 --> 00:26:08.401
I have great news.

578
00:26:08.402 --> 00:26:11.112
Hang on. hang on.
[chuckles] I wanna see this.

579
00:26:11.113 --> 00:26:12.363
Is this about the new merch?

580
00:26:12.364 --> 00:26:15.950
I want us to wear shirts that say.
"It's hard out here for a shrimp."

581
00:26:15.951 --> 00:26:16.910
I'll take a large.

582
00:26:16.911 --> 00:26:19.913
No. it is much better than that.

583
00:26:20.706 --> 00:26:23.876
I sold my share of
the truck to your dad.

584
00:26:25.711 --> 00:26:27.587
Now you guys can do it together.

585
00:26:27.588 --> 00:26:30.257
Thanks to psychological
something-ism.

586
00:26:32.342 --> 00:26:33.343
Are you insane?

587
00:26:34.303 --> 00:26:37.222
Do you know how much
shit I have with my dad?

588
00:26:37.806 --> 00:26:39.432
But I heard you guys
talking in the truck...

589
00:26:39.433 --> 00:26:41.601
Here's a thought:
Why not ask me?

590
00:26:41.602 --> 00:26:42.768
Hey. now.

591
00:26:42.769 --> 00:26:46.647
No. I was trying to do good.
I will totally undo it.

592
00:26:46.648 --> 00:26:49.108
So. then he'll know I
don't wanna work with him?

593
00:26:49.109 --> 00:26:50.736
This was our thing.

594
00:26:51.320 --> 00:26:52.612
Sean. wait.

595
00:26:52.613 --> 00:26:54.656
Nah. Fuck you. Liz.

596
00:26:55.949 --> 00:26:57.075
Damn it!

597
00:27:02.664 --> 00:27:04.917
- Babe...
- [sighs]

598
00:27:05.501 --> 00:27:06.543
Thank you for coming.

599
00:27:07.211 --> 00:27:08.503
I'm just glad you're here.

600
00:27:08.504 --> 00:27:10.087
Yeah. Well. Jennie said
she wouldn't speak to me

601
00:27:10.088 --> 00:27:11.923
unless I gave you three
minutes to say your piece.

602
00:27:11.924 --> 00:27:13.883
- [sighs]
- Ready to start?

603
00:27:13.884 --> 00:27:16.636
- Time's going now? Okay. I gotta focus.
- Mm-hmm.

604
00:27:16.637 --> 00:27:17.845
- We're going?
- Now.

605
00:27:17.846 --> 00:27:19.765
Okay. [sighs]

606
00:27:20.432 --> 00:27:23.018
So. believe it or not. Grace.
I know exactly how you feel

607
00:27:23.519 --> 00:27:26.647
because there is so much in my life
that I need to forgive myself for.

608
00:27:27.356 --> 00:27:29.399
[chuckles] And it's
not coming easy.

609
00:27:30.275 --> 00:27:32.611
There are some days I think
it might not come at all.

610
00:27:34.029 --> 00:27:36.531
But what I do know is
that this shit with Donny.

611
00:27:36.532 --> 00:27:39.450
it is a self-destructive stall.
Please don't look at your watch.

612
00:27:39.451 --> 00:27:41.118
- Just give me a li...
- I gotta get back.

613
00:27:41.119 --> 00:27:43.455
It's okay. It's what I deserve.

614
00:27:44.039 --> 00:27:47.251
[imitates trumpet]

615
00:27:48.836 --> 00:27:53.047
That's the noise that plays in my head
whenever I come in to save the day.

616
00:27:53.048 --> 00:27:54.465
Inappropriate?
We're being somber?

617
00:27:54.466 --> 00:27:56.593
[sucks teeth] No
regrets. Worth it.

618
00:27:57.094 --> 00:27:58.094
May I have the floor?

619
00:27:58.095 --> 00:27:59.720
Can you promise not
to slap anybody?

620
00:27:59.721 --> 00:28:01.473
We'll have to see
how this unfolds.

621
00:28:02.057 --> 00:28:03.100
Grace.

622
00:28:05.894 --> 00:28:07.436
I've been thinking
about friendship

623
00:28:07.437 --> 00:28:12.692
and about how friends are supposed
to be the people who understand you

624
00:28:12.693 --> 00:28:16.238
and who know what your
husband does for a living.

625
00:28:17.322 --> 00:28:21.367
But then I realized that I have
been listening to your friends

626
00:28:21.368 --> 00:28:23.578
make their character
witness statements.

627
00:28:23.579 --> 00:28:27.416
But you didn't get to hear them.
and I think that you should.

628
00:28:29.585 --> 00:28:30.835
This is from Kyra.

629
00:28:30.836 --> 00:28:33.881
She said. "I met
Grace in high school.

630
00:28:34.798 --> 00:28:39.177
- I was new and lonely. and..."
- [Kyra] <i>And she saved me.</i>

631
00:28:39.178 --> 00:28:41.680
She looked out
for the underdogs.

632
00:28:42.764 --> 00:28:45.851
And with the whole Donny thing. I
should have been looking out for her.

633
00:28:47.477 --> 00:28:52.649
When I had a miscarriage last year.
Grace took care of me all weekend.

634
00:28:53.233 --> 00:28:57.696
I knew Donny would give her hell for it.
but all she seemed to think about was me.

635
00:28:59.406 --> 00:29:01.992
You know what annoys
me about Grace? I...

636
00:29:02.576 --> 00:29:04.076
Okay. We're not gonna do Denise.

637
00:29:04.077 --> 00:29:06.120
[chuckles] There's always one.

638
00:29:06.121 --> 00:29:08.707
She doesn't like that you're
such a show-off at karaoke.

639
00:29:09.291 --> 00:29:10.459
Well. she's right. I am.

640
00:29:10.959 --> 00:29:13.836
- You wanna read yours?
- [stammers. chuckles]

641
00:29:13.837 --> 00:29:15.172
[clears throat]

642
00:29:17.216 --> 00:29:20.635
"I love my little sister
more than anyone."

643
00:29:20.636 --> 00:29:22.012
Mmm. [chuckles]

644
00:29:22.596 --> 00:29:27.600
"I used to think I needed to protect
her. because she is truly a light."

645
00:29:27.601 --> 00:29:29.019
[scoffs]

646
00:29:30.521 --> 00:29:32.147
"Donny tried to snuff it out.

647
00:29:33.482 --> 00:29:38.195
But in the end. her light was stronger
than I ever could have imagined.

648
00:29:39.988 --> 00:29:41.698
And I'm so glad it was."

649
00:29:47.955 --> 00:29:50.123
Don't listen to me.
Grace. Listen to them.

650
00:29:52.459 --> 00:29:53.460
What do you say?

651
00:29:54.044 --> 00:29:55.462
["Letting Go" playing]

652
00:30:18.986 --> 00:30:21.153
Did you consider the fact
that it's inappropriate

653
00:30:21.154 --> 00:30:22.989
for a doctor to date a patient?

654
00:30:22.990 --> 00:30:24.824
- We did.
- Yeah.

655
00:30:24.825 --> 00:30:26.951
And then we decided
we didn't give a shit.

656
00:30:26.952 --> 00:30:28.244
[all chuckle]

657
00:30:28.245 --> 00:30:30.914
Look. I don't really
need a new doctor.

658
00:30:31.790 --> 00:30:36.502
To be honest. Dr. Sykes. sh... she's really
a much better neurologist than you are.

659
00:30:36.503 --> 00:30:39.214
That's very sweet.
but also quite rude.

660
00:30:40.090 --> 00:30:45.929
I wanna give Julie a chance
to just be my girlfriend.

661
00:30:47.222 --> 00:30:49.807
You think you can attend
appointments as his partner

662
00:30:49.808 --> 00:30:52.476
and not as the
"world's best doctor"?

663
00:30:52.477 --> 00:30:54.312
Oh. you'll never see me again.

664
00:30:54.313 --> 00:30:56.565
[chuckles] I'll go
get some intake forms.

665
00:30:59.526 --> 00:31:01.527
- I like her.
- Yeah. I can tell.

666
00:31:01.528 --> 00:31:05.907
Which is why we are absolutely gonna
find you an ugly old man instead.

667
00:31:05.908 --> 00:31:07.450
N-No.

668
00:31:07.451 --> 00:31:09.745
This will be good to
keep you on your toes.

669
00:31:15.292 --> 00:31:18.211
And besides. you're a much
better kisser than she is.

670
00:31:18.212 --> 00:31:20.213
- You got that straight.
- Yeah.

671
00:31:20.214 --> 00:31:22.633
[imitates trumpet]

672
00:31:23.509 --> 00:31:27.303
That's the noise that plays in my
head whenever I come home to see you.

673
00:31:27.304 --> 00:31:28.764
Oh. Hey.

674
00:31:29.765 --> 00:31:31.015
It's also your hero noise.

675
00:31:31.016 --> 00:31:32.184
They're very similar.

676
00:31:33.310 --> 00:31:35.437
- What's going on?
- Jimmy came for dinner.

677
00:31:36.271 --> 00:31:38.981
[sighs] It's Wednesday.
so I thought. um...

678
00:31:38.982 --> 00:31:40.608
I thought we could
start a new tradition.

679
00:31:40.609 --> 00:31:41.984
[chuckles] Okay.

680
00:31:41.985 --> 00:31:46.113
I was just saying how interesting
it is that a Gemini like you

681
00:31:46.114 --> 00:31:49.117
ended up with a management
consultant like Charlie.

682
00:31:49.785 --> 00:31:50.993
That is crazy.

683
00:31:50.994 --> 00:31:52.453
I'm going to grab more wine.

684
00:31:52.454 --> 00:31:53.539
Okay.

685
00:31:55.207 --> 00:31:56.624
[inhales deeply]

686
00:31:56.625 --> 00:31:58.042
He's a management consultant?

687
00:31:58.043 --> 00:31:59.460
That's what it says
on his website.

688
00:31:59.461 --> 00:32:01.212
- He has a website?
- [chuckles]

689
00:32:01.213 --> 00:32:02.964
Beaujolais-Village.

690
00:32:02.965 --> 00:32:06.384
- 2019. for you to open. please.
- Oh. Whoa. Okay.

691
00:32:06.385 --> 00:32:07.760
- And will you please...
- Oh.

692
00:32:07.761 --> 00:32:09.303
Adorn the microgreens?

693
00:32:09.304 --> 00:32:11.514
Which I believe in French
means small greens.

694
00:32:11.515 --> 00:32:12.724
[chuckles]

695
00:32:16.937 --> 00:32:18.730
[speaks indistinctly]

696
00:32:27.531 --> 00:32:29.199
[breathes heavily. sniffles]

697
00:32:35.163 --> 00:32:37.249
Fuck! Fuck!

698
00:32:38.417 --> 00:32:40.419
[breathes deeply]

699
00:32:41.378 --> 00:32:42.628
[Connor] Hey. [chuckles]

700
00:32:42.629 --> 00:32:44.046
My dad put his watch on me

701
00:32:44.047 --> 00:32:47.426
and told me to walk around the block
four times so he can eat some fruit.

702
00:32:48.093 --> 00:32:49.802
[breathing heavily]

703
00:32:49.803 --> 00:32:52.013
- Are you... Are you all right?
- No.

704
00:32:52.014 --> 00:32:54.390
Don't make me talk.
I don't wanna talk.

705
00:32:54.391 --> 00:32:56.851
- [cries] I don't wanna talk.
- It's okay. No. it's okay.

706
00:32:56.852 --> 00:32:58.395
It's okay.

707
00:32:59.396 --> 00:33:02.231
I'm here. I'm...
What... What can I do?

708
00:33:02.232 --> 00:33:04.109
[breathing heavily]

709
00:33:06.612 --> 00:33:07.613
Whoa. Okay.

710
00:33:08.530 --> 00:33:09.531
What do you...

711
00:33:11.491 --> 00:33:12.491
Kiss me.
